  m_text: The FMEA is an established method in QM for error prevention. Possible
    risks of the system, as well as their causes and consequences, are determined
    and systematically presented. The critical system functions are evaluated in
    terms of severity, detection, and occurrence to subsequently determine a risk
    priority number. On this basis, optimisation measures are derived and directly
    implemented.
